{
  "texts": [
    "These signal stabilization (Janssen et al. 2022) data reduction steps are performed with two independent pipelines, EHT-HOPS (Blackburn et al. 2019) and the CASA-based (CASA Team 2022; van Bemmel et al. 2022) rPICARD software (Janssen et al. 2019a).",
    "These pipelines are described in more detail in M 87 * 2017 III and Sgr A * 2017 II.",
    "No significant algorithmic changes were made to the EHT-HOPS pipeline fringe fitting methods compared to the 2017 analysis.",
    "For the rPICARD pipeline, we now use a priori determined solutions for the typically ∼7.3 ns single-band and multi-band delay offsets of the phased ALMA instead of solving for these offsets using the ALMA-APEX baseline as was done for the 2017 data.",
    "The stabilized data are then loaded into the AIPS software package (Greisen et al. 2003), where a priori amplitude calibration is applied using the task APCAL to convert the correlation coefficients to a common flux density scale across the very heterogeneous EHT array."
  ]
}